# Chart the joelclaw Observational Memory Write Loop

## Destination

Joel's charter (2026-07-12, verbatim intent): *agent transcripts continuously
distilled into observations, efficiently, in a durable process, across the
joelclaw fleet.*

Reached when: a durable observer loop runs over pi/claude/codex session
transcripts fleet-wide, continuously (threshold/cadence, not on-demand),
distilling them into **observation pages** — `.svx` in a Brain section,
rendered at brain.joelclaw.com, nodes in the graph — each carrying provenance
(session id, machine, repos touched, commits via the change ledger) and
surviving a Joel read-through as *worth recalling*, not transcript sludge. A
reflector pass condenses aging observations without losing citations. The
distilled layer reaches every agent context (rhizomatic briefing + a recall
surface) — the ADR's functional bar: "every context we run in has the ability
to understand all of the work that we're doing."

## Notes

- **Prior art in-house**: the Bugle pipeline IS an observer (gather →
  normalize → pi extraction behind versioned schemas → open loops) — pointed
  at external streams. This map points the same discipline at the fleet's own
  session transcripts. Do not fork the philosophy: deterministic collection
  first, bounded pi judgment behind versioned schemas with receipts, fail
  loud.
- **Vision authority**: [agentic-memory-system-vision ADR](../../resources/decisions/agentic-memory-system-vision.svx)
  (accepted) — sessions are first-class memory surface; the bar is functional
  recall, not architecture. The [Mastra OM frame](https://mastra.ai/docs/memory/observational-memory)
  (Observer/Reflector, token-threshold triggers, async buffering, 5–40×
  compression, recall tool) is the reference model, adapted not copied.
- **House patterns**: Inngest durable functions are the joelclaw runtime for
  "durable process"; pi for all inference (no paid APIs); Typesense indexes
  sessions already; the session change ledger (Pi runtime v1) provides
  hash-proven session→commit attribution; graph.json v2 + wikilinks for
  structure; brainbench for honesty. `.brain` law: observations are `.svx`.
- **Privacy is inherited, with one new edge**: transcripts contain secrets,
  tokens, and third-party content. Observation pages are publications (they
  render on the paper) — the distiller needs a redaction boundary equivalent
  to the wiki's redact.ts BEFORE anything ships. Decided boundaries from
  `define-privacy-access-publication-boundaries` apply unchanged.
- **Efficiency is a stated requirement**: bounded token spend per day,
  observation only on new material (cursor over capture stream), compression
  ratios measured. Distillation quality > coverage — noise control is the
  hard half.
- **Storage decision (accepted 2026-07-12)**: files are truth, databases are projections — [decision record](../../resources/decisions/files-are-truth-databases-are-projections.svx). Observation pages live as `.svx` in git; Typesense/graph/ClickHouse only ever hold rebuildable views. Named exit triggers in the record; do not relitigate when a new database looks fun.
- **Skills**: `/skill:wayfinder`, `/skill:brain-first-workflow`,
  `/skill:session-search`, `/skill:effect-ts`, `/skill:joel-writing-style`.

## Decisions so far

<!-- one line per closed ticket: gist + link -->

- [Decide the Observation Schema and Brain Placement](./decide-observation-schema.svx) — per-session atoms (reflector composes threads later) as `.svx` in `dark-wizard/.brain/observations/` → `/user/observations/…`; v1 frontmatter w/ provenance + derivation.promptHash; extractors are body sections behind a versioned pi prompt; noise bar: no mutations + <15k tokens → index line, no page.
- [Define the Transcript Redaction Boundary](./define-transcript-redaction-boundary.svx) — memory covers ALL work: sensitive domains get `privacy: sensitive` pages (recallable, never rendered); secrets never persist even unrendered (git is publishing) — mandatory secret-scan before write, one retry then tombstone; local inference moves enforcement to persistence.
- [Decide the Observer Runtime and Trigger Topology](./decide-observer-runtime-topology.svx) — flagg-central HEADLESS HERDR SESSION (pi + local ds4-central, zero cost, transcripts never leave flagg) that can spawn observable sub-agent panes; supervisor canary for durability; gpt-5.6-terra as frontier comparator/reflector; continuous loop over indexed deltas.
- [Research Session Capture Coverage Across the Fleet](./research-session-capture-coverage.svx) — Pi+Claude on flagg+blaine are healthy (~43 conversations/day, same-day indexing); Codex delivery broken everywhere (→ fix-codex-capture-delivery); panda uncaptured (fine, decommissioning); change ledger is Pi-on-flagg only, so `commits` is best-effort elsewhere.

## Not yet specified

- Reflector condensation policy (cadence, thresholds, citation preservation).
- Recall surface design: fattened rhizomatic briefing + a `recall` tool over
  the distilled layer — which agents get it how, on which machines.
- Brainbench leg for observation quality ("worth recalling" rubric).
- Historical backfill of pre-loop sessions (months of transcripts exist).
- Cross-machine dedup when the same work appears in multiple sessions.
- ClickHouse event mirror of observer runs (telemetry, blessed 2026-07-12).
- Retention/compaction of raw observations after reflection.

## Out of scope

- External-stream observation (mail/Slack/Front/Discord) — the Bugle owns it.
- Public or multi-user anything; paid-API inference.
- Rebuilding session capture itself — capture exists; gaps found by the
  coverage research ticket get fixed, not redesigned.
